commentBody:
Another comment...

@Steve L noticed that there are no Ys in the puzzle, to avoid the confusion of whether a Y is a vowel or consonant.

I noticed something what cool. The constructor managed to maintained the pattern from one word to the next, as well. Between words, the empty black squares continue the pattern as if there were letters in them. For example, CASA_EDAM. The _ would have been a constant. It's like that all the way through, both across and down. And in the two places where there are two black squares together, the pattern still holds. UTILE_ _MUNI.

@Bob
th...
the comment fails are showing how impressive the construction was. no shade.

