Thanks.

@Gooberdog

I assume you meant to say ENTRIES rather than CLUES. 

Even so, the revealer VOWEL is perfectly clued. Every other letter of the GRID (including entries AND black squares) is indeed a vowel, if you consider each black square (or two or three) to be a continuation of the pattern. Every which way you look at the rows or columns the vowels alternate with consonants. For example, from 42A to 43A there are 3 black squares giving dEn vowel consonant vowel tOtAlEd.

@Mean Old Lady

I kicked myself when I figured out that 2D was AVEDA. I don’t use cosmetics, and typically don’t care much about what personal care products I use (just don’t make me bathe with Irish Spring).

But AVEDA makes (made?) a bath soap that smells fantastic and feels even better to use. We bought it regularly for a few years and then for some reason went back to Dial.

@Eric Hougland
Dial has an ingredient that causes instant rash on me...  it was the ONLY soap in the house when I was a teen, and I was "broken out in a rash" all the time.  Left for college (with a bar of Dial) but eventually I was out of college and in a job, and I went to a dermatologist:  his first act ws to nix "deodorant soaps"...within weeks my skin was clear as he dealt with other allergies as well.  
Dial is bad news!

